### For Momentum BC_XBTM & BC_XTOP
BC_XBTM & BC_XTOP (Momentum) will be automatically set to velocity_inlet (2) & convective outlet (3)
unless they were set to periodic (4) boundary conditions at the pre-processing step.

### For Thermal BC_T_XBTM & BC_T_XTOP:
* If XPRDIC is OFF: The inlet (XBTM) is set to Dirichlet using the mapped T_INF (from settings.in)
                    The outlet (XTOP) defaults to a convective outlet boundary.
* If XPRDIC is ON: The solver tracks the mean bulk temperature rise/fall (delta_T = T_avg_out - T_avg_in)
                   and applies it as an offset to the periodic ghost cells to balance the global heat flux.

### For Momentum BC_YBTM ~ BC_ZTOP;
0    : Solid wall boundary condition      (zero velocity components)
1    : Far field boundary condition       (u_normal = 0, d(u_tangential)/dx_i = 0) 

### For Thermal BC_T_YBTM ~ BC_T_ZTOP;
0    : Dirichlet (Constant Temperature). Use VAL_T to specify the target temperature.
1    : Neumann (Constant Heat Flux). Use VAL_T to specify the temperature gradient (dT/dn).

ICH   : Mean flow rate condition (0; Deactivate, 1; Activate)
ICONJG: Conjugate heat transfer condition (0; Constant temp., 1; Conjugate heat transfer) 